1
00:00:06,140 --> 00:00:08,540
=Fireworks=

2
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,860
=Episode 24=

3
00:00:12,839 --> 00:00:16,800
You think you're the only one
who knows how to prepare?

4
00:00:24,637 --> 00:00:25,712
(Bomb activated)

5
00:00:26,199 --> 00:00:27,160
No one moves.

6
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:30,719
The bomb detonator is in my hands.

7
00:00:30,719 --> 00:00:31,679
Anyone moves,

8
00:00:31,679 --> 00:00:33,479
and I'll blow you all!

9
00:00:34,479 --> 00:00:35,280
Jiang Xiao.

10
00:00:36,159 --> 00:00:37,479
You raised me.

11
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:40,000
So I suggest you turn back
before it's too late.

12
00:00:40,479 --> 00:00:41,600
Don't make any more mistakes.

13
00:00:43,039 --> 00:00:45,280
Shut up.

14
00:00:47,119 --> 00:00:49,359
You really are my good son.

15
00:00:50,119 --> 00:00:51,359
I raised you,

16
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:52,479
giving you everything,

17
00:00:52,479 --> 00:00:54,399
and this is how you repay me?

18
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:58,719
Fine. No one's leaving here alive today.

19
00:00:59,039 --> 00:01:00,840
Die, all of you!

20
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:01,375
(Bomb activated)

21
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,519
No way.

22
00:01:13,959 --> 00:01:15,120
Sorry.

23
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:17,519
I shouldn't be laughing
at a time like this,

24
00:01:17,719 --> 00:01:20,680
but you're just too stupid.

25
00:01:21,799 --> 00:01:23,400
You did this?

26
00:01:23,959 --> 00:01:25,719
You got tricked by those foreigners.

27
00:01:25,879 --> 00:01:28,319
The bombs they gave you
won't even explode.

28
00:01:28,799 --> 00:01:30,239
Their tech is outdated.

29
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,079
It's not even wireless.

30
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:34,239
As soon as the software crashes,

31
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:35,480
the bombs won't work.

32
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:37,840
So I just went ahead
and blocked it for you.

33
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,660
No need to thank me.

34
00:01:45,879 --> 00:01:46,680
Zechen,

35
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,680
don't forget.

36
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:50,079
Zemu's ashes are still in my hands.

37
00:01:50,319 --> 00:01:51,519
I haven't forgotten.

38
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:56,680
This punch is for me.

39
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:01,280
This punch is for Zemu.

40
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,640
You indirectly killed him.

41
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,799
I won't forgive you.

42
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:06,000
I...

43
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,520
And this punch is for Qiao Nian.

44
00:02:10,159 --> 00:02:12,039
You've taken her mom away for years.

45
00:02:13,319 --> 00:02:15,240
Now, you want to take Qiao Group too?

46
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:16,919
Zechen,

47
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:18,759
please, stop hitting me.

48
00:02:18,759 --> 00:02:21,439
I'll give you back Zemu's ashes, okay?

49
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,879
And?

50
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,000
Oh, I...

51
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:27,800
I'll confess...

52
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,400
I'll confess everything
about the foreign gangs to the police.

53
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,159
And I'll

54
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:35,599
destroy all the contracts
with Qiao Group.

55
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:38,039
I'll destroy everything. Please.

56
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:42,199
Zechen, let me go.

57
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,520
Please, let me go, Zechen.

58
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:44,960
(Jiang Xiao and his crew are arrested)
I can't go to jail!

59
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:47,280
Let me go, Zechen!

60
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,360
You're so beautiful.

61
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,199
Nian.

62
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:17,840
Mom.

63
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,439
Nian.

64
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,599
You look so beautiful today.

65
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:40,120
Mom, you look even more beautiful.

66
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,639
Let's sit down and have some snacks.

67
00:03:45,759 --> 00:03:48,280
Grandpa, how's your health lately?

68
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,840
I'm feeling much better now.

69
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,879
Nian, you don't need to worry about me.

70
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:54,360
Worry about yourself.

71
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:57,599
Tomorrow's your first day

72
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,919
at the company as the chairperson.

73
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,439
Make sure you don't mess up.

74
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:04,039
I know, Grandpa.

75
00:04:04,039 --> 00:04:05,120
Don't worry.

76
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,919
I won't let you down.

77
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,560
Alright.

78
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,400
Gosh.

79
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:13,759
I feel bad I couldn't
find your mom sooner

80
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,120
and let her suffer under Jiang Xiao.

81
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:20,399
Yunyi, I'm sorry.

82
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:22,800
I don't blame you.

83
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,800
You've taken such good care of Nian.

84
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,959
I should be thanking you.

85
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,079
I feel so bad.

86
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,360
Enough, Grandpa.

87
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,800
Try that cake and see if it's good.

88
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,439
Okay.

89
00:04:35,439 --> 00:04:36,639
Don't eat too much.

90
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,879
Alright.

91
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,639
Today, I'd like to thank my two friends.

92
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,959
Thank you, Wen Li, Song Che.

93
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,600
Thank you for helping me

94
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,680
save my mom

95
00:04:50,079 --> 00:04:51,920
and bringing Jiang Xiao to justice.

96
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,040
It's the least we could do.

97
00:04:54,839 --> 00:04:56,319
I wish you both eternal happiness.

98
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,319
Thank you.

99
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,199
Grandpa.

100
00:05:03,199 --> 00:05:04,000
Yes?

101
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:05,200
I'd like to toast to you.

102
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:07,959
Thank you for always being there for me,

103
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,839
protecting me as I grew up.

104
00:05:10,879 --> 00:05:13,079
You've handed the company
over to me now.

105
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,399
Don't worry.

106
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:16,199
I'll do my best.

107
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,560
I won't disappoint you.

108
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:20,879
Alright, I know you'll do well.

109
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:21,720
Thank you.

110
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,639
Drink less, Grandpa.

111
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:27,639
I will.

112
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:34,959
Mom, you've suffered
so much these years.

113
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,360
It's okay.

114
00:05:41,959 --> 00:05:43,160
I feel that...

115
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,319
as long as you're happy,

116
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:49,199
everything I've done is worth it.

117
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,560
Lastly...

118
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,199
I have to thank you.

119
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,199
Thank you, honey.

120
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,360
Thank you for always being there
for me and protecting me.

121
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:09,120
Every time I need you the most,

122
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,720
you're always right there beside me.

123
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,720
You're like fireworks in the night,

124
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,480
warming me and lighting up my world.

125
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,399
I feel so happy right now.

126
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:23,399
As long as you're happy,

127
00:06:24,399 --> 00:06:25,560
anything I do is worth it.

128
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,319
What do you want to do?

129
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:39,839
Right now,

130
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,800
you're the only family I have left.

131
00:06:45,399 --> 00:06:46,360
Don't worry.

132
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,480
Nothing will ever separate us again.

133
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,920
But I feel like it's not enough.

134
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,079
What's not enough?

135
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:58,680
I want to have more family.

136
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,240
Try this.

137
00:07:14,839 --> 00:07:18,079
See that? There's a reason he won.

138
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:19,639
You need to learn.

139
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,800
Shut up.

140
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,680
Just eat your food.

141
00:07:27,690 --> 00:07:28,800
What are you laughing about?

142
00:07:29,439 --> 00:07:32,120
I just think you two
are really a perfect match.

143
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,399
Have you thought about being together?

144
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:38,279
- She doesn't deserve me.
- He doesn't deserve me.

145
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,879
Let me announce something.

146
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:48,600
After I finish handling
some company matters,

147
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,480
I'm going back to London
to continue my art course.

148
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:54,720
This time, I'll be studying
computer science in London.

149
00:07:57,759 --> 00:07:59,040
- London?
- London?

150
00:07:59,287 --> 00:08:00,488
- You're going there too?
- You're going there too?

151
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:02,480
- Are you doing this on purpose?
- Are you doing this on purpose?

152
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:07,560
Alright.

153
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,959
If you two end up together,
don't forget to send me an invitation.

154
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,199
Come on, eat up.

155
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:22,600
(When Zemu was little,
he loved swimming in this river.)

156
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
(He always wanted
to become a fish in the river.)

157
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:07,279
Goodbye, Zemu.

158
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:37,919
This river is like Zemu's love.

159
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,720
He'll always be with us.

160
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,519
I'll be the same.

161
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:47,240
I'll always stay by your side.

162
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:53,480
That way,
Zemu's spirit will rest in peace.

163
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,200
Alright.

164
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,080
Don't be sad, okay?

165
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,279
Okay?

166
00:10:10,519 --> 00:10:12,240
Qiao Nian.

167
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,480
Qiao Nian, don't run.

168
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,799
Slow down.

169
00:10:18,799 --> 00:10:21,120
Hold my hand. Slow down.

170
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,360
Who's there?

171
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,279
Hello.

172
00:10:57,279 --> 00:10:59,240
You have a package at the lobby.

173
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:16,519
(Is this all a dream?)

174
00:11:16,519 --> 00:11:17,800
(The End)

175
00:11:20,330 --> 00:11:26,300
♪So many words unsaid,
the deeper we fall, the more we fear♪

176
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:34,180
♪Fate like a gamble,
locking us inside its game♪

177
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:38,020
♪Hearts at play, truth and lies,
who could ever know♪

178
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:41,820
♪Where this ends♪

179
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:49,100
♪I try to walk away,
yet still step into the fire♪

180
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:53,430
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

181
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:56,550
♪Love turns into pain♪

182
00:11:56,620 --> 00:12:00,740
♪Words betray us
until our eyes burn red♪

183
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:04,380
♪Yet I still want you close♪

184
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:08,550
♪Your tide breaks me,
and I fall for you again♪

185
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:11,860
♪Even if love becomes nothing♪

186
00:12:11,860 --> 00:12:16,430
♪When love and hate fade
into the crowd and the ice melts♪

187
00:12:16,430 --> 00:12:22,740
♪Does it mean we could meet again?♪

188
00:12:23,330 --> 00:12:27,520
♪Your heartbeat pulls me under,
and I lose myself♪

189
